Wood Partners, a major multifamily real estate developer, has finished the construction and debuted Alta Raintree Residences in Scottsdale, a new premium complex located on E Raintree Drive in the northern region of the desert city, one of the Phoenix Metro’s most desirable residential regions. The development has a total of 330 apartments with one-, two-, and three-bedroom floor designs. Each apartment has modern architectural finishes and high-quality interior packages, including stainless steel appliances, exquisite quartz kitchen counters with tile backsplash, electronic door entry, and wood-inspired plank flooring. Also Read: US$224 million construction loan secured for The HUB @ 2O2, Arizona Kohler®’s bathroom accessories with illuminated mirrors and frameless showers, as well as in-unit washer and dryer sets are also some of the apartment’s features. Select units also have additional upgrades including side-by-side refrigerators, double ovens, vent hoods, and wine refrigerators. Occupants of the Alta Raintree Residences in Scottsdale will have access to a plethora of unique shared amenities, including a Sky Lounge with expansive views of the McDowell Mountains, a resort-style pool with a tanning deck and jacuzzi, and an outdoor game courtyard and putting green. There is also an on-site pet park and multiple outdoor entertainment areas complete with grilling stations in addition to a fitness center featuring on-demand yoga, a meditation area, a Wi-Fi lounge, a conference area with micro-offices, a clubroom and an on-site library and speakeasy. Urbo Market and coffee bar, the on-site convenience market concept created by Wood Partners, will offer coffee, wine, gourmet snacks, and more to residents as well.